.\" termin.al-name: notes
.\" termin.al-usage: notes
.\" termin.al-summary: Open notes content.
.TH NOTES 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
notes \- Open notes content.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
notes
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Opens validated note publications beneath
.B ~/notes
as a hierarchical collection. Selecting a row opens its rendered Markdown document; returning from the document restores the collection and its selection.
.SH VIEWER
Use j/k or arrows to move, h/l or left/right to collapse and expand, g/G or Home/End to jump, Enter to toggle/open, and / to filter. Escape leaves filter editing first. From the collection, q, Escape or Ctrl+C returns to the shell. Mobile controls provide movement, Filter/Clear, Toggle, Open and Shell.
.SH FAILURES
Extra arguments are rejected. Missing or misclassified note content produces the stable content-unavailable diagnostic. Cancellation opens nothing.
.SH LIMITS
Loading traverses at most 100 virtual entries to a maximum depth of 100 beneath
.BR ~/notes .
.SH NOTES
The collection is read-only and transient. Closing it preserves the owning pane's transcript, history and working directory.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ notes
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
blog(1), projects(1), open(1)
